records.addlTxt:
Defendant Scott Michael Lee in court, in custody, with attorney Craig S. Powell.    District Attorney's Office Law Intern supervised by Pablo Galaviz appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Plea Colloquy.

Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 7.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Counts 1, 2, 3 and 4 are dismissed and read in.

Sentencing argument by the State.  Statement by defendant's father. Sentencing argument by Atty. Powell.  Statement by defendant.


The Court Orders the Following:

Imposed Sentence of:
5 Years Imprisonment (Credit - 38 days )
- 2 Years of Initial Confinement
- 3 Years of Extended Supervision

Conditions of Extended Supervision:
- AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
- Be involved in a 12 step program within 30 days and obtain a mentor;
- Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
- No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
- No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
- Any valid prescription drugs must be taken in the manner in which they are prescribed;
- Inform agent of all prescriptions;
- Sign Medical Release for Agent;
- Perform  20 hours of community service each year of extended supervision with the 20 hours in the 3rd year to be completed within the first 10 months;
- Within 3 months obtain a valid license;
- Operate a Motor Vehicle with a Valid Drivers License;
- Maintain/Obtain full time employment;
- Provide DNA sample if not yet provided  and pay surcharge;

Buy Money:  $300.00 to be paid during by 25% of prison earnings only and during the first 2 years of extended supervision joint and several with co-defendant

Cost: $268.00 
DNA surcharge: $250.00
(To be paid as a condition of extended supervision)

Defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program
Defendant is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program

Felony warnings, immigration warnings,  voting rights and firearms warnings given.
